0Ohio%2C%20said%20the%20whole%20reason%20he%20chose%20this%20gym%20was%20that%20it%20didn't%20have%20a%20binding%20contract%20%E2%80%94%20he%20assumed%20that%20when%20he%20no%20longer%20wanted%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20membership%2C%20he'd%20be%20able%20to%20get%20out%20of%20it.%20After%20the%20parent%20company's%20customer-service%20reps%20told%20him%20they%20couldn't%20assist%20him%20online%20or%20over%20the%20phone%20and%20did%20not%20offer%20him%20an%20alternate%20route%2C%20Mattison%20reached%20out%20to%20his%20bank%2C%20which%20ultimately%20canceled%20the%20card%20he'd%20used%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20membership%20and%20told%20him%20plenty%20of%20customers%20had%20trouble%20getting%20out%20of%20similar%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bank%20even%20said%20that%20they%20see%20this%20happening%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20Mattison%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20customers%20having%20trouble%20with%20cancellations.%20%26quot%3BThey%20said%20the%20good%20news%20was%20that%20I%20only%20gave%20them%20a%20card%20number%20instead%20of%20my%20actual%20account%20number.%20Then%20it's%20a%20lot%20more%20hassle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Mattison%20was%20glad%20to%20have%20found%20a%20solution%2C%20it%20took%20three%20months%20to%20get%20free.%20He%20described%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20worst%20experience%20I've%20ever%20had%20with%20any%20type%20of%20membership.%26quot%3B%20And%20he's%20not%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20companies%20have%20gotten%20increasingly%20savvy%20at%20trapping%20customers%20in%20what%20are%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bdark%20patterns%2C%26quot%3B%20drawing%20them%20in%20with%20a%20shiny%20new%20product%20or%20discounted%20subscription%20that%20ends%20up%20being%20burdensome%20to%20get%20out%20of.%20The%20tactics%20companies%20use%20to%20keep%20people%20on%20the%20treadmill%20of%20recurring%20charges%20can%20range%20from%20slick%2C%20attractive%20product%20design%20to%20deceptive%20fraud.%20And%20in%20a%20world%20where%20people%20seldom%20read%20the%20fine%20print%2C%20consumers%20don't%20have%20much%20recourse%20when%20they%20find%20they%20can't%20cancel%20something%20they%20no%20longer%20want.%20In%20a%202022%20survey%20from%20C%2BR%20Research%2C%20respondents%20estimated%20they%20spent%20an%20average%20of%20%2486%20a%20month%20on%20subscriptions%2C%20but%20when%20they%20were%20asked%20to%20individually%20break%20down%20their%20monthly%20payments%20based%20on%20their%20bank%20statements%2C%20they%20were%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20spending%20an%20average%20of%20%24219.%20Additionally%2C%2042%25%20of%20respondents%20indicated%20they'd%20forgotten%20they%20were%20continuing%20to%20pay%20for%20products%20they%20no%20longer%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20attempt%20to%20combat%20these%20practices%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20on%20Wednesday%20finalized%20a%20rule%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BClick-to-Cancel%26quot%3B%20that%20addresses%20the%20issue.%20The%20rule%2C%20which%20goes%20into%20effect%20in%20180%20days%2C%20would%20require%20most%20businesses%20to%20make%20the%20cancellation%20of%20subscriptions%20just%20as%20easy%20as%20the%20sign-up%20process%2C%20as%20well%20as%20protect%20customers%20from%20other%20dark%20pattern%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20new%20rule%20is%20a%20strong%20stab%20at%20solving%20the%20issue%2C%20companies%20have%20spent%20years%20perfecting%20their%20methods%20of%20roping%20in%20new%20customers.%20Florencia%20Marotta-Wurgler%2C%20a%20consumer-law%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University%2C%20told%20me%20that%20most%20people%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20smart%20they%20think%20they%20are%2C%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20traps%20such%20as%20hidden%20fees%2C%20misleading%20website%20layouts%2C%20or%20confusing%20terms%20and%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20lots%20of%20biases%20that%20consumers%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Marotta-Wurgler%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20care%20more%20about%20the%20immediate%20rewards%20than%20the%20cost%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20services%20are%20created%20or%20designed%20to%20exploit%20these%20biases%20to%20really%20dangle%20the%20shiny%20object%20that%20they%20want%20and%20then%20just%20to%20hide%20the%20cost%20later%20or%20when%20consumers%20might%20forget.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20isn't%20an%20accident%20that%20people%20who%20want%20to%20cancel%20a%20subscription%20often%20have%20to%20navigate%20a%20web%20of%20bureaucracy%20and%20confusion.%20Erin%20Witte%2C%20the%20director%20of%20consumer%20protection%20at%20the%20Consumer%20Federation%20of%20America%2C%20says%20companies%20have%20spent%20years%20honing%20dark-pattern%20tactics%20to%20maximize%20recurring%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20all%20by%20design.%20This%20is%20a%20way%20that%20companies%20can%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Witte%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20automatically%20recurring%20subscription%20plans%20and%20free-trial%20conversions%2C%20they%20basically%20capitalize%20on%20people%20not%20consenting%20actively%20to%20something%20over%20and%20over%20again.%20When%20you've%20forgotten%20that%20you%20signed%20up%20for%20it%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20easier%20to%20just%20keep%20charging%20and%20charging%20and%20charging.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20dark%20patterns%20usually%20involve%20two%20steps.%20First%2C%20the%20company%20makes%20it%20easy%20or%20desirable%20to%20opt%20for%20the%20recurring%20charge.%20Marotta-Wurgler%20pointed%20to%20Amazon's%20%26quot%3Bsubscribe%20and%20save%26quot%3B%20feature%2C%20in%20which%20the%20online%20retail%20giant%20offers%20a%20discount%20for%20agreeing%20to%20have%20a%20certain%20product%20delivered%20monthly.%20The%20website%20makes%20the%20subscription%20the%20default%20option%20during%20checkout%2C%20causing%20many%20consumers%20to%20enroll%20without%20realizing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20company%20keeps%20people%20subscribed%20using%20%26quot%3Bnegative%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20contracts%20in%20which%20it%20interprets%20a%20consumer's%20silence%20or%20failure%20to%20act%20as%20an%20agreement%20to%20continue%20purchasing%20the%20product.%20These%20frequently%20take%20the%20form%20of%20subscriptions%20that%20automatically%20renew%20unless%20the%20consumer%20cancels%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20primary%20way%20people%20find%20themselves%20paying%20for%20a%20service%20they%20didn't%20realize%20they%20were%20still%20being%20billed%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20consumers%20have%20submitted%20public%20comments%20to%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20about%20their%20frustrations%20with%20subscription%20cancellations.%20%26quot%3BI%20and%20many%20others%20have%20continuously%20been%20charged%20without%20consent%20for%20renewal%20of%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20person%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20charging%20should%20be%20abundantly%20clear%20from%20the%20start%2C%20as%20ultimately%20whether%20or%20not%20the%20consumer%20wants%20to%20pay%20should%20be%20the%20consumers%20choice%20and%20not%20the%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prevalence%20of%20these%20tactics%20and%20of%20consumer%20anger%20prompted%20the%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20to%20issue%20guidance%20last%20year%20saying%20that%20companies%20were%20at%20risk%20of%20violating%20federal%20law%20should%20they%20fail%20to%20clearly%20disclose%20the%20terms%20of%20a%20negative-option%20service%20or%20make%20consumers%20jump%20through%20hoops%20to%20cancel%20a%20subscription.%20A%20CFPB%20official%20told%20me%20that%20the%20agency%20had%20seen%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%20of%20problems%26quot%3B%20with%20vague%20disclosures%20and%20rage-inducing%20cancellation%20processes%20in%20which%20consumers%20have%20to%20repeatedly%20speak%20with%20customer-service%20representatives%20for%20unreasonably%20long%20periods%2C%20preventing%20them%20from%20articulating%20their%20intent%20to%20cancel%20a%20subscription%20because%20they%20oftentimes%20cannot%20remain%20on%20hold%20long%20enough%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20these%20issues%20have%20led%20to%20litigation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20bureau%20sued%20TransUnion%20in%202022%20over%20allegations%20that%20the%20credit-reporting%20agency%20%26quot%3Bused%20an%20array%20of%20dark%20patterns%20to%20trick%20people%20into%20recurring%20payments%20and%20to%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20cancel%20them.%26quot%3B%20These%20tactics%2C%20the%20bureau%20alleged%2C%20included%20crafting%20a%20website%20with%20misleading%20buttons%20to%20give%20consumers%20the%20impression%20that%20they%20could%20access%20a%20credit%20score%20for%20free%3B%20instead%2C%20clicking%20the%20button%20would%20sign%20them%20up%20for%20recurring%20monthly%20charges%20using%20credit-card%20information%20they'd%20provided%20to%20verify%20their%20identity.%20TransUnion%20said%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20bureau's%20claims%20were%20%26quot%3Bmeritless%20and%20in%20no%20way%20reflect%20the%20consumer-first%20approach%20we%20take%20to%20managing%20all%20our%20businesses.%26quot%3B%20A%20decision%20on%20the%20case%20is%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20are%20lured%20into%20subscriptions%20across%20all%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Marotta-Wurgler%20said%20that%20without%20enhanced%20regulation%2C%20such%20as%20a%20requirement%20to%20disclose%20terms%20of%20a%20subscription%20upfront%20rather%20than%20conceal%20it%20in%20the%20fine%20print%2C%20companies%20have%20few%20incentives%20to%20change%20their%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we're%20talking%20about%20consumer%20protection%2C%20the%20burden%20is%20always%20on%20the%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20the%20consumer%20needs%20to%20make%20the%20choice%2C%20and%20it's%20on%20the%20consumer%20to%20know%20what%20they're%20signing%20up%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20business%20leaders%20oppose%20stricter%20regulations%20like%20the%20FTC's%20new%20Click-To-Cancel%20rule%20because%20they're%20concerned%20that%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20get%20out%20of%20subscriptions%20could%20cause%20consumers%20to%20accidentally%20miss%20out%20on%20products%20they%20still%20might%20want.%20The%20Association%20of%20National%20Advertisers%20argued%20in%20a%20public%20comment%20to%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20sellers%20are%20required%20to%20enable%20cancellation%20through%20a%20single%20click%20or%20action%20by%20the%20consumer%2C%20accidental%20cancellations%20will%20become%20much%20more%20common%2C%20as%20consumers%20will%20not%20reasonably%20expect%20to%20remove%20their%20recurring%20goods%20or%20services%20with%20just%20one%20click.%26quot%3B%20The%20association%20added%20that%20accidental%20cancellations%20could%20cause%20customers%20to%20miss%20out%20on%20essential%20items%2C%20like%20food%2C%20and%20it%20would%20be%20burdensome%20for%20the%20customer%20to%20once%20again%20have%20to%20go%20through%20the%20sign-up%20process%20to%20renew%20their%20subscriptions.%20Witte%20dismissed%20this%20sort%20of%20thinking%20as%20short-sighted%2C%20arguing%20that%20companies%20could%20benefit%20from%20making%20their%20interfaces%20more%20consumer-friendly.%20%26quot%3BActual%20affirmative%20consent%20from%20a%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20Witte%20said%2C%20would%20establish%20trust%20between%20the%20consumer%20and%20the%20company%2C%20boosting%20loyalty.%20The%20FTC's%20new%20rule%20would%20make%20this%20sort%20of%20assent%20a%20reality%3A%20companies%20now%20have%20to%20adjust%20their%20sign-up%20processes%20so%20consumers%20explicitly%20confirm%20they%20want%20a%20subscription%20that%20automatically%20renews%20and%20understand%20the%20terms%20before%20they%20are%20charged%2C%20and%20companies%20have%20to%20be%20able%20to%20prove%20that%20consumers%20knew%20what%20they%20agreed%20to%20before%20they%20signed%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20FTC%20really%20wants%20to%20make%20sure%2C%20with%20this%20rule%2C%20that%20consumers%20are%20getting%20what%20they%20want%20and%20what%20they%20understand%20and%20what%20they%20agree%20to%2C%20and%20that%20businesses%20are%20serving%20consumers%20that%20want%20their%20product%2C%20not%20people%20who%20have%20just%20forgotten%20about%20a%20subscription%20or%20have%20had%20too%20much%20trouble%20getting%20out%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Witte%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20free%20trials%20and%20confusing%20websites%20can%20be%20a%20money-sucking%20headache%20for%20consumers%2C%20many%20of%20the%20methods%20of%20keeping%20people%20on%20the%20hook%20are%20legal.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20however%2C%20the%20tactics%20used%20by%20subscription%20services%20can%20tip%20into%20outright%20fraud.%20Celebrity%20endorsements%20are%20a%20go-to%20method%20to%20convince%20consumers%20to%20put%20down%20their%20credit-card%20information%2C%20but%20sometimes%20the%20celebrity%20doesn't%20even%20know%20the%20company%20is%20using%20their%20likeness%20to%20boost%20a%20product.%20Mark%20Cuban%20can%20attest%20to%20this%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%26quot%3BShark%20Tank%26quot%3B%20star%20told%20me%20he'd%20been%20featured%20%26quot%3Bthousands%20of%20times%26quot%3B%20in%20ads%20for%20a%20keto-gummies%20subscription%20service.%20The%20ads%20make%20it%20appear%20as%20if%20Cuban%20endorsed%20the%20product%2C%20which%20promises%20health%20benefits%20and%20weight%20loss%2C%20but%20the%20endorsement%20is%20fake%2C%20and%20Cuban%20said%20he%20hadn't%20even%20heard%20of%20the%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20federal%20laws%20designed%20to%20prevent%20companies%20from%20lying%20in%20their%20advertising%2C%20Cuban%20argued%20that%20it%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20waste%20of%20time%26quot%3B%20to%20take%20any%20legal%20action%20against%20the%20company%2C%20like%20sending%20them%20cease-and-desist%20orders%2C%20because%20the%20companies%20frequently%20close%20and%20open%20different%20legal%20entities%20to%20stay%20ahead%20of%20these%20claims.%20Some%20customers%20who%20were%20deceived%20by%20the%20ads%20have%20emailed%20Cuban%20asking%20for%20help%20getting%20out%20of%20the%20subscription.%20He%20forwarded%20me%20examples%20of%20a%20few%20of%20the%20emails%20he%20received%3A%20One%20customer%20said%20the%20gummy%20ad%20claimed%20that%20all%20%26quot%3BShark%20Tank%26quot%3B%20investors%20had%20endorsed%20the%20product%2C%20but%20she%20ended%20up%20being%20charged%20an%20additional%20%24200%20for%20a%20product%20the%20company%20added%20alongside%20the%2030-day%20supply%2C%20prompting%20her%20to%20immediately%20email%20the%20company%20to%20cancel%20the%20order.%20%26quot%3BThis%20higher%20transaction%20will%20cause%20my%20checking%20account%20to%20be%20over%20and%20will%20cause%20my%20rent%20and%20utilities%20to%20bounce%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20Cuban%20recommended%20everyone%20who%20signed%20up%20for%20the%20service%20to%20call%20their%20bank%20to%20cancel%20the%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20dark%20patterns%20tip%20into%20outright%20scams%20and%20fraudulent%20subscription%20practices%2C%20the%20experience%20of%20being%20deceived%20can%20take%20a%20toll%20on%20consumers%20financially%20and%20mentally.%20Witte%20said%20consumers%20often%20feel%20like%20these%20situations%20are%20their%20fault.%20In%20retrospect%2C%20customers%20think%20they%20should%20have%20noticed%20red%20flags%20or%20read%20the%20fine%20print%20before%20entering%20their%20credit-card%20information.%20But%20companies%20have%20sophisticated%20technology%20to%20prevent%20you%20from%20looking%20into%20any%20red%20flags%20such%20as%20subscription%20pop-up%20windows%20that%20advertise%20the%20perks%20of%20a%20product%20but%20do%20not%20disclose%20the%20fine%20print.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20easy%20for%20consumers%20to%20look%20back%20and%20use%20their%20hindsight%20and%20say%2C%20'Man%2C%20I%20really%20wish%20I%20had%20seen%20that%20or%20looked%20more%20carefully%20at%20this%2C'%26quot%3B%20Witte%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20not%20always%20just%20about%20consumer%20awareness%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20really%20is%20much%20more%20about%20the%20product%20of%20manipulative%20design%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ERachel%20VonSiebenhoven%2C%2052%2C%20signed%20up%20for%20a%20membership%20at%20her%20local%20massage%20parlor%20in%20Colorado%20in%202012%20to%20treat%20herself.%20She%20said%20that%20she%20initially%20paid%20%2455%20a%20month%20but%20that%20the%20price%20gradually%20increased%20while%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20service%20declined.%20After%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20she%20decided%20she%20was%20no%20longer%20getting%20her%20money's%20worth%20and%20began%20the%20process%20of%20canceling%20her%20membership%20in%202023.%20However%2C%20VonSiebenhoven%20said%20it%20took%20months%20of%20back-and-forth%20with%20the%20parlor%20to%20discuss%20refund%20options%20because%20the%20terms%20were%20murky%20on%20whether%20she%20could%20get%20money%20back%20after%20canceling%20her%20membership%2C%20all%20while%20she%20was%20charged%20for%20services%20she%20wasn't%20using.%20As%20of%20September%2C%20she%20was%20still%20trying%20to%20get%20her%20money%20back%20and%20didn't%20reach%20a%20resolution%20with%20the%20parlor%20on%20whether%20canceling%20her%20membership%20would%20cause%20her%20to%20forfeit%20any%20potential%20refund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20been%20a%20constant%20battle%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20working%20full%20time%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20school%20for%20my%20MBA%2C%20so%20I%20have%20no%20time.%20So%20I'm%20hoping%20they%20just%20canceled%20it%20because%20if%20not%2C%20I'm%20just%20paying%20for%20something%20and%20still%20not%20able%20to%20get%20anything%20out%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20could%20be%20some%20relief%20on%20the%20horizon%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Click-to-Cancel%20rule%20is%20a%20key%20step%20that%20could%20result%20in%20tangible%20benefits%20for%20consumers%2C%20Witte%20said%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she%20noted%20that%20it%20does%20not%20include%20a%20requirement%20for%20companies%20to%20send%20consumers%20annual%20notices%20about%20their%20subscriptions%20and%20provide%20them%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20cancel%2C%20which%20would%20have%20been%20an%20effective%20safeguard.%20The%20FTC%20is%20likely%20being%20as%20cautious%20as%20possible%20to%20avoid%20lawsuits%20against%20the%20rule%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarotta-Wurgler%20described%20the%20initiative%20as%20a%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%20%26quot%3BCompanies%20have%20been%20able%20to%20get%20away%20with%20this%20because%20we've%20been%20playing%20Whac-A-Mole%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarotta-Wurgler%20argued%20that%20requiring%20structural%20changes%20in%20business%20practices%2C%20like%20implementing%20a%20bolstered%20federal%20standard%20for%20disclosing%20terms%2C%20would%20help%20prevent%20consumers%20from%20being%20lured%20into%20dark%20patterns.%20More%20attention%20at%20the%20state%20and%20federal%20levels%20would%20also%20help.%20Along%20with%20litigation%20from%20the%20CFPB%2C%20state%20attorneys%20general%20have%20pursued%20legal%20action%20against%20big%20companies%20over%20hard-to-cancel%20subscriptions.%20Last%20year%2C%20Letitia%20James%2C%20New%20York's%20attorney%20general%2C%20sued%20SiriusXM%20over%20claims%20that%20the%20radio%20company%20trapped%20customers%20in%20subscriptions%20and%20maintained%20a%20complicated%20and%20burdensome%20cancellation%20process.%20SiriusXM%20called%20the%20allegations%20%26quot%3Bmeritless%26quot%3B%20and%20asked%20for%20the%20case%20to%20be%20dismissed.%20The%20case%20is%20still%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustries%20have%20mastered%20techniques%20to%20maximize%20their%20profits%20by%20crafting%20their%20business%20models%20in%20confusing%20ways%20that%20can%20lure%20customers%20into%20a%20subscription%20without%20realizing%20it.%20With%20government%20attention%2C%20there's%20potential%20for%20change%20%E2%80%94%20but%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20burden%20is%20on%20the%20consumer%20to%20be%20vigilant%20or%20risk%20losing%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20be%20really%20time-intensive%20and%20confusing%20and%20burdensome%2C%20and%20that's%20frustrating%20to%20people.%20So%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20losing%20money%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20wasting%20a%20lot%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Witte%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20that%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fayelet-sheffey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAyelet%20Sheffey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20economic%20policy%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-subscriptions-nightmare-recurring-payments-cancellation-company-tricks-trap-customers-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729331281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67127c3bfd8ede6c99e3c81e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-subscriptions-nightmare-recurring-payments-cancellation-company-tricks-trap-customers-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Companies%20are%20using%20shadowy%20sign-up%20tactics%20and%20difficult%20cancelation%20processes%20to%20keep%20Americans%20trapped%20in%20subscriptions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-subscriptions-nightmare-recurring-payments-cancellation-company-tricks-trap-customers-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HDFC%20Bank%20Q2FY25%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20increases%205%25%20to%20Rs%2016%2C820%20cr%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729330997000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A