%2F%2Fwfhresearch.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FWFHResearch_updates_October2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESurvey%20of%20Working%20Arrangements%20and%20Attitudes%3C%2Fa%3E%20looks%20at%20how%20much%20the%20ability%20to%20work%20from%20home%20is%20worth%20to%20workers%3B%20the%20survey%2C%20which%20has%20been%20ongoing%20since%20May%202020%2C%20is%20conducted%20in%20monthly%20waves%20of%20thousands%20of%20Americans%20ages%2020%20to%2064.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20September%20survey%20of%209%2C457%20Americans%20finds%20the%20typical%20worker%20who%20has%20worked%20from%20home%20at%20some%20point%20since%202020%20said%20they%20would%20require%20an%20average%20of%20around%207.6%25%20more%20pay%20to%20clock%20in%20fully%20in-person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20currently%20work%20from%20home%20at%20least%20one%20day%20a%20week%2C%20hybrid%20or%20remote%20work%20is%20worth%20the%20same%20as%20a%209.6%25%20pay%20raise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20to%20be%20hybrid%20is%20more%20valuable%20for%20some%20groups%20than%20others.%20Nicholas%20Bloom%2C%20a%20Stanford%20University%20economist%20who%20helped%20spearhead%20the%20WFH%20research%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20workers%20%26quot%3Bin%20their%2030s%2C%20with%20kids%20and%20a%20university%20degree%26quot%3B%20said%20they'd%20need%20a%2010%25%20to%2015%25%20raise%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20office%20full-time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20sense%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-boom-millennials-not-gen-z-boomers-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOlder%20millennials%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20a%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20continued%20push%20for%20work%20from%20home%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-high-earners-moved-office-work-from-home-remote-work-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20moved%20further%20away%20from%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20started%20having%20younger%