ernment%20has%20been%20going%20ahead%20with%20its%20religious%20persecution%20without%20impunity.%20In%20its%20latest%20salvo%2C%20they%20have%20clamped%20down%20on%20all%20churches%20-%20Catholic%20and%20Protestant%20-%20in%20the%20country%20by%20ordering%20the%20pulling%20out%20of%20images%20of%20Jesus%20and%20his%20replacement%20with%20images%20of%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20according%20to%20a%20US%20government%20report%20on%20anti-religious%20activities%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20continuing%20saga%20of%20'Sinicization'%2C%20China%20has%20pushed%20to%20align%20all%20religions%20or%20shape%20all%20religions%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20doctrines%20of%20the%20CCP%20(Communist%20Party%20of%20China)%20and%20the%20customs%20of%20the%20majority%20Han%20Chinese%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20came%20to%20power%20in%20March%202013%2C%20authorities%20have%20insisted%20on%20adhering%20to%20Communist%20Party%20values%20like%20speaking%20only%20in%20Mandarin%20Chinese%20and%20rejecting%20all%20foreign%20influence%20that%20may%20endanger%20China's%20unity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20Sinicization%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESinicization%20is%20the%20procedure%20in%20which%20non-Chinese%20groups%20or%20societies%20are%20integrated%20into%20Chinese%20culture.%20The%20process%20includes%20the%20adoption%20of%20Chinese%20language%2C%20culture%2C%20ethnic%20identity%20and%20societal%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESinicization%20is%20also%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Chinese%20government's%20policy%20of%20subordinating%20religious%20groups%20to%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20China's%20(CCP)%20political%20agenda.%20The%20policy%20of%20Sinicization%20has%20been%20started%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Xi%20Jinping%20and%20has%20transformed%20China's%20religious%20landscape.%20Some%20of%20the%20government-introduced%20actions%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1)Placing%20CCP%20supporters%20as%20religious%20leaders%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2)Changing%20the%20designs%20of%20religious%20places%20like%20mosques%2C%20churches%20etc%20with%20CCP-approved%20architecture%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3)%20Mixing%20CCP%20publicity%20into%20religious%20doctrines%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4)%20Outlawing%20non-CCP-backed%20religious%20activities%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20officially%20an%20atheist%20country%20but%20it%20recognises%20five%20religions%3A%20Buddhism%2C%20Catholicism%2C%20Daoism%2C%20Islam%2C%20and%20Protestantism.%20The%20practice%20of%20any%20other%20faith%20is%20formally%20prohibited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Chinese%20constitution%20(Article%2036)%20mentions%20that%20citizens%20'enjoy%20the%20freedom%20of%20religious%20belief'%20and%20bars%20discrimination%20based%20on%20religion%2C%20the%20law%20controls%20religion%20by%20preventing%20state%20organs%2C%20public%20organisations%20etc.%20It%20dissuades%20citizens%20from%20following%20any%20faith.%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20anti-religion%20campaign%20initiated%20by%20President%20Xi%20has%20the%20backing%20of%20all%20state-controlled%20religious%20organisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20a%20feeling%20that%20homegrown%20religions%20like%20Confucianism%2C%20Buddhism%2C%20and%20Daoism%20do%20not%20challenge%20the%20CCP's%20rule%20but%20others%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20does%20China%20fear%20Buddhists%20and%20Christians%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tibetan%20Buddhists%20staying%20in%20China's%20Tibetan%20region%20have%20faced%20high%20levels%20of%20religious%20persecution.%20Chinese%20authorities%20keep%20a%20firm%20eye%20on%20the%20daily%20operations%20of%20their%20major%20monasteries.%20Despite%20China's%20strict%20vigilance%2C%20reports%20of%20detainments%20and%20torture%20of%20monks%20and%20nuns%20for%20refusing%20to%20denounce%20the%20Dalai%20Lama%20often%20surface.%20Followers%20of%20the%20Dalai%20Lama%20too%20have%20been%20ordered%20to%20replace%20his%20photos%20with%20those%20of%20the%20Chinese%20leaders.%20China%20fears%20'outside%20influence'%20from%20the%20exiled%20Dalai%20Lama.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20US%20government%20report%20made%20public%20recently%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20government%20has%20ordered%20the%20removal%20of%20crosses%20from%20churches%2C%20replaced%20images%20of%20Jesus%20Christ%20or%20the%20Virgin%20Mary%20with%20pictures%20of%20President%20Xi%2C%20required%20the%20display%20of%20CCP%20slogans%20at%20the%20entrances%20of%20churches%2C%20censored%20religious%20texts%2C%20imposed%20CCP-approved%20religious%20materials%2C%20and%20instructed%20clergy%20to%20preach%20CCP%20ideology.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Vatican%20can't%20take%20up%20the%20issue%20of%20repression%20of%20Catholics%20estimated%20to%20be%20around%2010%20to%2012%20million%2C%20since%20it%20does%20not%20have%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Vatican's%20recognition%20of%20Taiwan%20and%20a%20dispute%20over%20the%20bishop%20appointment%20process%20in%20China%20have%20been%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20dispute.%20Of%20late%2C%20both%20countries%20have%20come%20to%20a%20sort%20of%20agreement%20whereby%20the%20Pope%20has%20recognised%20several%20Chinese%20state-appointed%20bishops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20Christians%20have%20rejected%20the%20government-controlled%20churches%20completely%20and%20instead%20are%20worshipping%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20China%20targeted%20Muslims%3F%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuslims%20form%20around%201%20to%201.5%25%20of%20China's%20population.%20Reports%20of%20China's%20genocide%20against%20the%20Uyghur%20population%20and%20other%20mostly-Muslim%20ethnic%20groups%20in%20the%20north-western%20region%20of%20Xinjiang%20have%20been%20circulated%20for%20years%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20China's%202020%20census%2C%20there%20are%20more%20than%2011%20million%20Uyghurs%20in%20this%20region.%20The%20Uyghurs%20were%20brutalised%20because%20they%20spoke%20their%20language%2C%20similar%20to%20Turkish%2C%20and%20considered%20themselves%20culturally%20and%20ethnically%20close%20to%20Central%20Asian%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20one%20million%20Uyghurs%20have%20been%20held%20captive%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20in%20a%20large%20network%20of%20what%20China%20calls%20its%20're-education%20camps'%2C%20and%20sentenced%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20to%20prison%20terms.%20There%20has%20been%20mass%20sterilisation%20to%20control%20the%20Uyghur%20population%20and%20thousands%20have%20been%20enlisted%20to%20work%20as%20forced%20labourers%20in%20farms%20and%20factories%20put%20up%20by%20China.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20have%20banned%20their%20religious%20practices%20in%20the%20region%20and%20made%20mosques%20and%20tombs%20non-operational.%20Despite%20the%20hue%20and%20cry%20from%20human%20rights%20groups%20and%20the%20world%20at%20large%2C%20China's%20atrocities%20on%20Uyghurs%20didn't%20cease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETill%20very%20late%2C%20Hui%20Muslims%20had%20been%20lucky%20to%20avoid%20the%20tight%20control%20of%20the%20Chinese%20government%20as%20the%20latter's%20focus%20remained%20on%20the%20Uyghur%20Muslims%20in%20the%20Xinjiang%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020-21%2C%20China%20targeted%20the%20Hui%20Muslim%20community%20by%20removing%20the%20domes%20and%20minarets%20from%20thousands%20of%20mosques%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20Chinese%20authorities%20then%2C%20like%20now%2C%20felt%20that%20the%20domes%20are%20signs%20of%20foreign%20Saudi%20and%20Arabic%20religious%20influence.%20They%20demolished%20domes%20as%20they%20were%20symbolic%20of%20Islamic%20architecture%20-%20and%20were%20not%20Chinese%20in%20origin.%20This%20was%20part%20of%20an%20ongoing%20push%20to%20Sinicize%20Muslims%20to%20make%20them%20traditionally%20Chinese.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20process%2C%20mosques%20were%20closed%20and%20the%20mosque%20properties%20were%20acquired%20by%20the%20government%2C%20and%20imams%20were%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReactions%20from%20the%20world%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20China%20has%20repeatedly%20denied%20all%20allegations%20and%20continues%20to%20rubbish%20charges%20that%20it%20is%20carrying%20out%20oppression%20of%20the%20Uyghur%20population%20and%20other%20minorities.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Western%20nations%20have%20called%20out%20China%20several%20times.%20They%20presented%20a%20draft%20resolution%20to%20request%20a%20discussion%20in%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20about%20the%20Xinjiang%20report%20in%20October%202022.%20The%20draft%20resolution%20failed%20by%20a%20slim%20margin%20of%20two%20votes.%20But%20many%20countries%20have%20been%20silent%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20ten%20other%20nations%20abstained%20from%20voting%20in%20the%20UN%20against%20China%20over%20the%20human%20rights%20situation%20in%20the%20Xinjiang%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20officially%20India%20took%20a%20stand%20that%20the%20community's%20human%20rights%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Brespected%26quot%3B.%20Amidst%20border%20issues%2C%20India%20has%20been%20treading%20cautiously%20on%20geo-political%20issues%20with%20China%20on%20international%20forums.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20response%20of%20many%20countries%20on%20the%20Uyghur%20issue%20has%20been%20based%20on%20political%20calculations%20on%20how%20they%20have%20aligned%20with%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729313940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fqo5q2uh8_chinese-president-xi-jinping-reuters_625x300_15_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-chinas-continued-persecution-of-religious-minorities-6823501%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China's%20government%20has%20been%20going%20ahead%20with%20its%20religious%20persecution%20without%20impunit