3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20Belgian%20court%20has%20opened%20an%20investigation%20into%20allegations%20of%20war%20crimes%20by%20an%20Israel%20Defence%20Forces%20(IDF)%20soldier%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20Belgian%20Federal%20Prosecutor's%20Office%20launched%20a%20probe%20into%20a%20dual%20Belgian-Israeli%20national%20serving%20in%20the%20IDF%2C%20who%20is%20in%20his%20early%20twenties.%20The%20soldier%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20in%20a%20suburb%20of%20Brussels%2C%20and%20serves%20in%20the%20IDF's%20elite%20Multidimensional%20%26quot%3BGhost%26quot%3B%20(Refaim)%20sniper%20unit%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fisrael-news%2Farticle-825183%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20investigation%20centres%20around%20accusations%20that%20the%20soldier%20targeted%20unarmed%20civilians%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%20The%20complaints%20suggest%20that%20uninvolved%20civilians%20were%20deliberately%20shot%2C%20violating%20international%20laws%20protecting%20non-combatants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Belgian-Palestinian%20Association%20(ABP)%20filed%20the%20complaint%20that%20triggered%20the%20investigation.%20Belgian%20law%20allows%20the%20prosecution%20of%20its%20citizens%20for%20crimes%20committed%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Belgian%20Federal%20Prosecutor's%20Office%20confirmed%20the%20investigation%20on%20Friday%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20aims%20to%20verify%20whether%20the%20alleged%20war%20crimes%20were%20committed%20by%20the%20sniper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20case%20follows%20a%20report%20by%20Palestinian%20journalist%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fytirawi%2Fstatus%2F1842242729436201158%5C%22%3EYounis%20Tirawi%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20accused%20the%20Refaim%20sniper%20unit%20of%20deliberately%20targeting%20unarmed%20civilians.%20According%20to%20Tirawi%2C%20his%20findings%20were%20corroborated%20by%20a%20senior%20American%20officer%20serving%20within%20the%20unit.%20The%20officer%20allegedly%20shared%20evidence%20and%20recounted%20instances%20where%20the%20unit%20fired%20on%20civilians%2C%20even%20when%20there%20was%20no%20threat%20to%20IDF%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Refaim%20Unit%2C%20to%20which%20the%20accused%20soldier%20belongs%2C%20has%20reportedly%20been%20active%20in%20Gaza%20since%20October%202023.%20This%20elite%20Israeli%20military%20unit%2C%20consisting%20of%2021%20soldiers%2C%20includes%20members%20from%20various%20nationalities.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20Belgian%20under%20investigation%2C%20the%20unit%20comprises%20three%20Americans%2C%20two%20French%20citizens%2C%20one%20German%2C%20and%20one%20Italian%2C%20among%20others.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20against%20the%20Belgian%20sniper%20draws%20heavily%20on%20interviews%20conducted%20by%20Tirawi.%20According%20to%20the%20journalist%2C%20the%20senior%20American%20officer%20provided%20chilling%20testimony%2C%20likening%20Gaza%20to%20the%20biblical%20city%20of%20Sodom%2C%20which%20was%20destroyed%20due%20to%20its%20sins.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20officer%20allegedly%20referred%20to%20Gaza's%20residents%20as%20%26quot%3BAmalekites%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20term%20from%20the%20Old%20Testament%20often%20used%20in%20historical%20contexts%20to%20describe%20enemies%20of%20the%20Israelites.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729311720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fn1i3h0v8_ghost-unit-_625x300_19_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fprobe-into-israels-elite-ghost-sniper-unit-accused-of-war-crimes-in-gaza-6823326%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Belgian%20court%20has%20opened%20an%20investigation%20into%20allegations%20of%20war%20crimes%20by%20an%20Israel%20Defence%20Forces%20(IDF)%20soldier%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Gaza.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv