see%20the%20posts%20of%20the%20person%20who%20blocked%20them.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20could%20force%20victims%20of%20abuse%20to%20choose%20between%20their%20safety%20and%20speech%20on%20X%2C%20one%20advocate%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20recently%20announced%20it's%20changing%20the%20way%20the%20social%20media%20platform's%20block%20function%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20blocking%20a%20user%20means%20that%20account%20can%20no%20longer%20see%20the%20posts%20of%20the%20user%20who%20blocked%20them.%20But%20X%20said%20this%20week%20that%20would%20change%20soon%2C%20though%20it%20did%20not%20specify%20when.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EInstead%2C%20the%20updated%20block%20function%20will%20still%20allow%20the%20blocked%20person%20to%20see%20the%20posts%20of%20the%20user%20who%20blocked%20them%20%E2%80%94%20as%20long%20as%20that%20user%20has%20a%20public%20account%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20will%20be%20unable%20to%20engage%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20block%20can%20be%20used%20by%20users%20to%20share%20and%20hide%20harmful%20or%20private%20information%20about%20those%20they've%20blocked.%20Users%20will%20be%20able%20to%20see%20if%20such%20behavior%20occurs%20with%20this%20update%2C%20allowing%20for%20greater%20transparency%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20X%20engineering%20team%20said%20in%20a%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECritics%20of%20the%20change%20say%20it%20could%20make%20X%20less%20safe%20for%20some%20users%2C%20such%20as%20victims%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-basic-income-program-domestic-violence-survivors-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edomestic%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20harassment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX%20did%20not%20provide%20comment%20on%20these%20concerns%20when%20reached%20by%20BI%2C%20instead%20referring%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FXEng%2Fstatus%2F1846605254864888180%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20X%20engineering%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3Bbig%20day%20for%20stalkers%20and%20harassers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20X%20user%20wrote%20in%20response%20to%20the%20announcement.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fevildeadthing%2Fstatus%2F1846611747727134945%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20got%20more%20than%2089%2C000%20likes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20blocking.%20It's%20supporting%20stalking%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FHeatherThomasAF%2Fstatus%2F1846662936242409668%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euser%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20do%20I%20block%20people%20whom%20I've%20blocked%20for%20security%20(stalking)%20reasons%3F%26quot%3B%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FBKatie617%2Fstatus%2F1846614222727196891%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euser%3C%2Fa%3E%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnything%20that%20gives%20an%20abusive%20individual%20power%20and%20control%20over%20the%20victim%20should%20be%20considered%20carefully%20by%20Twitter%2C%26quot%3B%20Adam%20Dodge%2C%20founder%20of%20End%20Tech-Enabled%20Abuse%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20mere%20knowledge%20that%20a%20person%20who%20is%20seeking%20to%20harm%20a%20victim%20can%20monitor%20their%20social%20media%20posts%20puts%20that%20victim%20in%20an%20unsafe%20position.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDodge%20said%20that%20this%20change%20in%20the%20block%20function%20could%20lead%20to%20some%20victims%20going%20into%20a%20mode%20of%20hypervigilence%2C%20which%20can%20have%20a%20severe%20impact%20on%20their%20emotional%20and%20physical%20wellbeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDodge%20said%20he%20expects%20some%20people%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20victims%20who%20criticize%20this%20change%20by%20telling%20them%20they%20should%20just%20make%20their%20account%20private%2C%20but%20he%20said%20that's%20blaming%20the%20victim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20recent%20post%20about%20the%20change%2C%20X%20directed%20users%20who%20wanted%20more%20control%20over%20who%20could%20see%20their%20posts%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.x.com%2Fen%2Fsafety-and-security%2Fhow-to-make-x-private-and-public%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epage%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20explains%20how%20they%20can%20make%20their%20account%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDodge%20said%20victims%20should%20be%20able%20to%20have%20their%20account%20be%20public%20if%20they%20choose%2C%20and%20that%20they%20should%20be%20empowered%20to%20block%20users%20who%20are%20harassing%2C%20stalking%2C%20or%20abusing%20them.%20There%20are%20also%20people%20who%20need%20a%20public%20X%20account%20for%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20result%20in%20victims%20being%20forced%20to%20choose%20between%20safety%20and%20their%20right%20to%20speech%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20and%20we%20should%20never%20be%20putting%20victims%20in%20that%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20workarounds%20to%20the%20current%20blocking%20system.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20blocked%20user%20could%20simply%20create%20a%20new%20account%20to%20view%20the%20posts%20of%20the%20user%20who%20has%20blocked%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20it%20is%20true%20that%20the%20current%20blocking%20system%20used%20by%20social%20media%20platforms%20isn't%20perfect%2C%20it%20typically%20creates%20some%20measure%20of%20a%20barrier%20to%20guard%20against%20toxic%20behavior%20and%20bad%20situations%20on%20the%20platform%2C%26quot%3B%20Dominic%20Sellitto%2C%20a%20clinical%20assistant%20professor%20of%20management%20science%20and%20systems%20at%20the%20University%20at%20Buffalo%20School%20of%20Management%20who%20researches%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwebsites-know-who-you-are-data-brokers-privacy-online-shopping-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigital%20privacy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20all%2C%20creating%20another%20account%20takes%20effort%2C%20and%20the%20typical%20harassing%20user%20on%20the%20platform%20may%20just%20move%20on%20if%20they%20cannot%20see%20a%20user's%20account%20who%20has%20blocked%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESellitto%20said%20consumers%20still%20have%20some%20power%20over%20their%20privacy%2C%20and%20that%20they%20can%20choose%20not%20to%20use%20a%20platform%20if%20they%20do%20not%20support%20its%20policies.%20He%20acknowledged%2C%20though%2C%20that%20this%20can%20be%20difficult%20for%20people%20whose%20accounts%20are%20tied%20to%20their%20work%2C%20personal%20brand%2C%20or%20even%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20it%20is%20something%20that%20every%20user%20should%20consider%20with%20any%20of%20their%20online%20presences%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20are%20encountering%20toxic%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-block-function-change-victims-domestic-abuse-safety-privacy-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729297012000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6711b247a0a0cc14f221e7b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-block-function-change-victims-domestic-abuse-safety-privacy-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Under%20an%20upcoming%20change%20blocked%20users%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20will%20still%20be%20able%20to%20see%20the%20posts%20of%20users%20who%20blocked%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40businessinsider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-block-function-change-victims-domestic-abuse-safety-privacy-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl